ACADEMIC USE NOTICE

This software is primarily intended for academic research and educational purposes. 
Users who publish research utilizing this computational framework should provide 
appropriate attribution in their methods sections, clearly indicating that analyses 
represent computational projections based on established pharmacokinetic models 
with parameters derived from literature sources.

DISCLAIMER

The computational models and simulations provided in this software generate 
theoretical predictions and should not be interpreted as experimental measurements. 
While parameter values are derived from published literature, actual biodistribution, 
toxicity, and efficacy outcomes depend on specific experimental conditions, 
formulation details, and biological systems. Users assume full responsibility for 
proper interpretation and application of computational results.

Presentation of computational projections as experimental data without proper 
disclosure constitutes scientific misconduct and violates ethical research standards. 
All results generated using this framework must be clearly labeled as computational 
or theoretical in nature, with appropriate citations to source literature for model 
parameters.

COMMERCIAL USE

Organizations interested in commercial applications of this software should contact 
the authors regarding licensing arrangements and collaborative opportunities. 
Commercial use includes but is not limited to pharmaceutical development, diagnostic 
applications, and medical device design incorporating the computational methodologies 
provided herein.
